                <note rend="inline" type="source">841D.24/27: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Ireland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gray</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="9" xml:id="d159fn9">This telegram was based on reply to
                        inquiry made to Henry L. Stimson, Secretary of War.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-09-20T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 20, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>64. Your no. 81, September 12, 10 p.m. There are no surplus rifles available for
                    sale at this time. All rifles which were declared surplus have been already
                    disposed of to foreign governments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
